    p.btext In the winter of 1606, three English ships, the Susan Constant, the Godspeed and the Discovery, started across the Atlantic under the command of Captain Christopher Newport. They carried 105 men, intending to settle at Roanoke Island, where an English colony had disappeared twenty years before, but they were driven further north by a storm.

